The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 October is 3,799 (439.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 October, there were 257 new confirmed cases (29.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 September, there were 165 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 56% (92 extra cases).
